ACR (Adaptive Combat Rifle)    

With ability to rapidly change calibers, barrel lengths and stock
configurations, the Bushmaster ACR adapts to varied conditions like no
rifle that has come before it. In minutes, without tools, it will go from
5.56mm to 6.8mm to 6.5mm by swapping the bolt head, barrel and magazine.
With an exchange of stocks, barrels and accessories, it transforms from a
close quarters weapon to a designated marksman platform. Simply put, the
Bushmaster ACR is the highest evolution of modular rifle utility. This
rifle is built specifically for law enforcement and tactical applications -
with Bushmaster's unrivaled standards for durability and precision. They've
nearly doubled barrel life and reduced maintenance with the addition of an
innovative protective coating. This is also featured on action components
for dramatically reduced wear and enhanced operation. For the ultimate
blend of strength and reduced weight, they used rugged, high density
composite for the hand guard, lower receiver and stock. The heart of the
ACR is their gas piston operating system. It's torture tested and proven
reliable in the most brutal conditions on the planet. From the magazine
release and fire selector to the non reciprocating charging handle,
ambidextrous controls optimize user effectiveness. Add Bushmaster's
hallmark commitment to quality down to the slightest ingredient, and you
have a platform that's a natural fit for any operator and every mission.

Ruger SR9c 9mm Subcompact Pistol 

The SR9c compact pistol has the same slim 1.27" grip width (across safety levers) as the full-sized SR9. It comes with two magazines, for both capacity and grip size. The standard magazine holds 10 rounds, and a second with a grip adapter that holds 17 rounds, instantly transforming the smaller, compact grip into a full-sized 9mm grip. The 3.50" barreled pistol features an integral accessory rail that accommodates most lights and lasers. The SR9c compact pistol also features high-visibility 3-Dot sight, serrations are located on the front portion of the slide, making it easier to both manipulate the slide and to press check the chamber. The SR9c is available with a glass-filled nylon frame and through-hardened slide in either a brushed stainless or blackened finish. Just like the original, full-sized SR9, the SR9c is loaded with modern safety features like a 1911-style ambidextrous manual safety, internal trigger bar interlock and striker blocker, trigger safety, magazine disconnect, plus a visual and tactile loaded chamber indicator.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Hakim  FTF only   wanted to move today
postcontent:
I have an Egyptian Hakim in 8mm it's a neat but different rifle I'm looking to sell or trade The Hakim Rifle (70,000 produced) is an accurate, reliable, gas operated semi-automatic rifle. It was originally designed by the Swedes and produced as the AG-42 Ljungman for the Swedish Army. The tooling and design were later sold to the United Arab Republic (Egypt), and the Hakim was produced there during the 1950's and 60's. The adjustable gas operated system is very simple and is not unlike the U.S. M16 rifle.

The Hakim features the proven and very strong tipping bolt system like the FN49, Russian SKS and French MAS56 rifles. Available in 8 mm Mauser caliber, 192 grain (12 g) bullet only, it is a finely machined (expensive to produce), sturdy semi-automatic rifle of the highest quality. The Hakim has a removable 10 round magazine intended to be reloaded with 5 round stripper clips (8 mm Mauser).

Bore and rifeling are in excellent condition, not counterbored. The M91's are getting hard to find especially with all of the attachments. title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare G98/40 (M43) Rifle
postcontent:
More pictures on request!

For any collectors out there you know just how rare this rifle is. Barely 100k rifles made across 6 years of WW2. This variant is a 1943 model. This is basically the Hungarian M35 that was modified to the specifications of Germany. It fires the 8x57 Mauser cartridge, accepts K98 bayonets, and some other minor details. Has the right petina, has the factory rear sight leaf adjuster (very hard to find, most broke and were swapped with K98 sight adjusters). Bore is okay, a little fuzzy but it shoots straight as an arrow. title: For Trade:  .308 Carbine
postcontent:
This is an FR-8 in 7.62 NATO/.308 for sale. Excellent condition. Someone put on a rubber buttpad on it at some time in it's past but original buttplate contour appears to be intact- could be put back to stock configuration with an $8 plate from Numrich. Has an arsenal stock repair behind the bolt.

FR-8 rifles were developed during late 1950s in Spain during their transition from military bolt action rifles to new, select-fire CETME Mod.58 assault rifles, chambered for then-new 7.62x51 NATO ammunition. The FR letters stand for "Fusil Refromando", and both FR-7 and FR-8 rifles are conversions of the earlier Mauser type bolt action rifles, which were in abundance at the time because of adoption of new, more effective guns.
The FR-8 rifles were converted from Spanish Model 1943 rifles, which are based on Model 1898 Mauser action, also known as "Large ring" Mauser action. Conversions included new barrels, inserted spacers in magazines (to accommodate shorter rounds), shortened forends and new iron sights. 
The FR-8 rifle is a manually operated bolt action rifle. It employs Mauser type rotary bolt with two frontal locking lugs and single rear lug (FR-7 bolt has no rear safety lug), and Mauser-type extractor which provides controlled feed. Cartridges are fed from integral box magazine with 5-round capacity, which can be loaded using stripper clips or loose rounds. Barrel is equipped with muzzle brake / flash hider, which also can be used to launch NATO-standard rifle grenades. The short tube, located below the barrel, has mostly cosmetic purpose, as it serves to provide bayonet mount interface. Its inner space also can be used to store front sight adjustment tool or small cleaning kit. The iron sights consist of adjustable, hooded front sight and combination aperture/V-notch rear sight, which is made in the form of rotating disc. The rear sight disc has V-notch for 100 meters range and three apertures for 200, 300 and 400 meters range.
Bayonets and slings from CETME's will work with this rifle.

Bore is excellent and finish is in great shape. I've seen several in the past with no finish left on the bolt handle, but it looks like this one hasn't been used very much. These rifles are somewhat rare and have just about doubled in value in the past couple years, and will probably continue to go up.
Comes with a box of soft points.

I'd be willing to take partial or whole trades if you have something interesting. Not looking for hunting rifles. Would like to find a stainless revolver in .357, or milsurp rifles I don't already have. 
Buyer must be willing to sign a receipt. Will not ship.
Any questions, just ask.
